This species is distinguished as follows: vertex black; mandible outer surface black, upper surface yellow, teeth reddish brown; clypeus with large yellow spot on each side; narrow yellow line on gena on hind orbit (
Figs 8
, 
10
); mesoscutellum entirely yellow or with thin medial black stripe; second metasomal tergum with broad posterior transverse band, not extended laterally (
Figs 8, 10
). Female armature present, in ventral view with lobes short and with shallow central depression (
Fig. 12
), in lateral view, posterior and ventral sides perpendicular, not directed downward at apex (
Figs 8
, 
11
); male genitalia with paramere long, about three-quarters length of gonostipes (
Fig. 14
); paramere in lateral view with dorsal margin straight (
Fig. 13
), without slight depression.
